reviews.review_text:
So far so good. (this is essentially a copy from the other show on this date...with a few modifications)

This shows just came in. A matrix of an SBD and an AUD source. Now...there are two uploads for this date and they do sound different. Unlike the other one, this one has more SBD dubbed in as the creater noted.  I think this is a better sounding version compared to the other date.  So I would stick with this one.

I just listened to Lazy > Sup and it was good! Peppy, good mixing of all the instruments. I think something happened to Keith's piano during the second half of the year because it doesn't sound the same as the first half of the year. Anyway...Supplication is a very good version. That song has a tendency for everyone to get out-of-sync, but during this performance it builds to a nice crescendo and carries on through the end of the song.

I'm also listening to Scarlet > Fire and it would rank between 5 and 10 best for 1977.  You are able to hear all of the band, they are generally in sync, and there is a fairly interesting segue between the two songs.  Fairly memorable but nothing to blow your socks off.  It starts off slow and not coordinated, only hearing a few instruments.  Not all that spacey either, but it just works.

So far 4/5 sound, 4/5 show.
Top Notch Highlights: Looks Like Rain, Lazy Lightning, Supplication, Sunrise, St. Stephen, Terrapin Station

Put the Pipes down and LISTEN!! I had a tape of this given to me on tour with a brother of mine who bought one of my drums I sold and I got his photography and Jay B's who went to school with me at TESC. What is wrong with you people??? The Trucking on this is one of the finest ever, so prove me wrong and send your downloads of better to john kersting at yahoo dot com. I am waiting. Meanwhile, I am putting this on my full sized 70's Klipshes and cranking it to 11 and dancing more 20 somethings under the table. 61 is going to be the shit with Sister Carol playing my ballroom Feb, 18th 2017 with 300 great friends. LOL.
